    {
        "content": "<p>fitzgen opened <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13354\">PR #13354</a> from <code>fitzgen:alias-region-entity</code> to <code>bytecodealliance:main</code>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Generalize from</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">enum</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">AliasRegion</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">Heap</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">Table</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">Vmctx</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>into a proper entity, allowing users to define arbitrary numbers of custom alias<br>\nregions.</p>\n<p><code>MemFlagsData</code> grows a <code>region: PackedOption&lt;AliasRegion&gt;</code> field instead of<br>\nbitpacking the alias region with the rest of its flags.</p>\n<p>The CLIF text format is also updated to support alias region declarations in the<br>\nfunction header, e.g. <code>region0 = 0 \"heap\"</code>, with memflags referencing regions by<br>\nentity name instead of the old hardcoded keywords.</p>\n<p>Depends on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13353\">https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13353</a></p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 594928702,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778697261
