        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1779469383
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> cfallin created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13354#discussion_r3290016323\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Maybe we could move the definition here instead of defining it in <code>ir</code> and aliasing it?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 597055460,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1779469383
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> cfallin created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13354#discussion_r3290009885\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Eek -- unsafe-transmute: can we add a const constructor if we need one instead?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 597055461,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1779469383
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> cfallin created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13354#discussion_r3290006190\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>comment nit: same as <code>MemFlagsData</code>'s <em>previous</em> representation, but we've now moved it solely into this type (and composed the outer struct around it), no? It might be good to also move the bitpacking comment here (to the field) since we discarded it above.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 597055462,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1779469383
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>fitzgen updated <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13354\">PR #13354</a>.</p>",
